cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.MM

This paper is primarily focused on the problem of Single Image Super-Resolution (SISR) using deep neural networks. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new framework for optimizing the generator network in the feature space of a features extractor network, which involves collaboration between the two networks. This aspect of the paper is related to the field of machine learning, specifically deep learning, and could be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the choice of objective loss function and its impact on the quality of super-resolved images, which is a topic in the field of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of satellite images as an example of a domain that is far from the ImageNet domain, which suggests that the paper could be relevant to the field of computer graphics (cs.GR). Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed framework in the context of SISR, which is a topic in the field of multimedia (cs.MM).
